<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Bartoli Wins Sunday's Tour of Romagna Cycle Race </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, September 6 (Xinhua) -- World Cup leader Michele Bartoli
outsprinted fellow Italians Germano Pierdomenico and Stefano
Cecchin
to win 195-kilometer Sunday's Tour of Romagna cycling race.
</P>
<P>
Bartoli clocked four hours, 50.37 minutes at an average speed
of 40.197 kph.
</P>
<P>
Austrian Gerrit Glomser finished fourth after beating Spain's
Oscar Freire Gomez.
</P>
<P>
The top ten finishers were clocked in the same time as the
winner.
</P>
</TEXT>
