<HEADLINE> New Coach Brings Victory to Quanxing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 6 (Xinhua) -- Newly-appointed coach Chi
Shangbin Sunday had the Chinese international Libing and his
injury time header to thank as Sichuan Quanxing edged Qingdao
Hainiu 1-0 at the 20th round of Chinese first division soccer
league.
</P>
<P>
Chi, ex-coach of national champions Dalian Wanda who took over
the struggling Quanxing only on three days ago, breathed a sigh
of relieve when center forward Li back-headed the goal into the
net in the dying minutes to set the winning tone for his new co
aching career.
</P>
<P>
Quanxing is now moving one step further to stand at fifth on
the table with 27 points.
</P>
<P>
Wuhan Hong Jilong has been keeping up its impressive
performances since the arrival of former national coach Qi
Wusheng a month ago and scored a convincing 3-1 win over
Vanguards Huandao to extend their winning streak to four games.
</P>
<P>
Beijing Guo'an continued their recent dismal form which sent
them crashing out of the FA Cup quarter-finals last week by
playing out a goalless draw with unfancied Shenyang Haishi.
</P>
<P>
Defending champions Dalian Wanda again proved a class of their
own as two goals from Swede stars Stefan Lindgvist and Hans
Eklund powered them to a 2-1 away win over Guangzhou Apollo.
</P>
<P>
The result left them atop in the standings with an awesome 48
points from a 15-3-2 record, 11 points higher than second-placed
Shanhai Shenhua, who crushed Guangzhou Songri 3-0 on the home
soil.
</P>
<P>
Elsewhere, the Chinese Army nipped Shandong Taishan 1-0 at
home while Shenzhen Ping'an forced an away goaless draw with
Yanbian Aodong. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
