<HEADLINE> Ethiopia to Host Meeting for Tokyo African </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, September 6 (Xinhua) -- Ethiopia announced Sunday
that the third meeting of the preparatory committee for the
second Tokyo International Conference on African development
(TICAD II) will be held in Addis Ababa from September 7 to 8,
1998.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a news briefing held here, Mulatu Teshome,
Vice-Minister of Economic Development and Cooperation, said the
main purpose of the third meeting is to finalize the draft agenda
for action, which will be adopted at TICAD II in October, this
year.
</P>
<P>
Mulatu recalled that the TICAD II preparatory committee was
launched in November, 1997, with Senegal, Zimbabwe and Ethiopia
selected to host TICAD II preparatory committee meetings.
</P>
<P>
Kunio Katakura, Japanese Ambassador to Ethiopia, said at the
news briefing that the theme of the TICAD II is "future
generation in Africa".
</P>
<P>
The ambassador said the conference will set target for
fighting poverty which is still reprevailing in Africa.
</P>
<P>
The Associate Administrator of the United Nations Development
Program (UNDP), Rafeeuddin Ahmed, said that African countries
themselves will be taking the lead as they have done in two
previous preparatory committees and other different preparatory
meetings organized.
</P>
<P>
Ahmed stressed the role played by the private sector in
promoting development of Africa and expressed his hope that
private sector will take place not only among African countries
themselves but also from the north as well as the south-south
cooperation.
</P>
<P>
The TICAD, convened by the UNDP, the Global Coalition for
Africa and the Japanese government, held its first meeting in
October 1993.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
