<DOCNO> XIE19980907.0010 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Stroyev: Consolidation Option to Emerge at Roundtable </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, September 6 (Xinhua) -- Russian Federation Council
Speaker Yegor Stroyev said here Sunday that a political roundtable
meeting "will result in a consolidating option that will help us
unite the nation."
</P>
<P>
"There can be peace only under one condition: if people meet
each other halfway without demonstrating ambitions," Stroyev told
reporters after meeting Miguel Martinez of the Inter-Parliamentary
Council.
</P>
<P>
The roundtable meeting, to be attended by President Boris
Yeltsin and deputies of both houses of parliament, was scheduled
for Monday.
</P>
<P>
In his talks with Martinez, the speaker of the upper house of
parliament reiterated his objection to Western loans to Russia.
</P>
<P>
"I personally am opposed to any Russian borrowings abroad,"
Stroyev said.
</P>
<P>
"They hamper us, cause contradictions between the oligarchs and
lead to everyone trying to get a bigger slice of the loan while
the people don't get anything anyway," the Interfax news agency
quoted Stroyev as saying.
</P>
<P>
"A country controlling 25 to 40 percent of the world's natural
resources has no right to go on begging around the world," he
said.
</P>
<P>
"If we finally give priority to domestic production, working
people, our national economy, even if it is a private economy with
banks, commercial and state, operating in the framework of
democracy and accord, I think we will get out of the
difficulties," he said.
</P>
<P>
Russia now owes 130 billion U.S. dollars in foreign debt and
more than 70 billion dollars in internal debt.
</P>
<P>
"The nation should reach agreement and after that start working
and creating material values," Stroyev said.
</P>
<P>
After the Monday roundtable meeting, the State Duma, or lower
house of parliament, will take a second vote on Chernomyrdin's
premiership.
</P>
<P>
The State Duma overwhelmingly rejected Chernomyrdin' candidacy
last Monday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
