<HEADLINE> Chinese State Councilor Meets U.N. Official </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XIAMEN, September 7 (Xinhua) -- State Councilor Wu Yi said
here today that the Chinese government underlines the role of the
U.N. Conference on Trade and Development.
</P>
<P>
She said China believes that both the U.N. Conference on Trade
and Development and the World Trade Organization are important
parts of multilateral trade system, and play an indispensable
role.
</P>
<P>
Wu said this while meeting with Rubens Ricupero,
secretary-general of the U.N. Conference on Trade and Development,
who is here for the Second China Fair for International Investment
and Trade scheduled to open tomorrow morning.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese government will continue to support and participate
in the activities arranged by the U.N. Conference on Trade and
Development, she said, adding that the Conference will promote
economic and trade cooperation between nations, thanks to support
from the developing countries.
</P>
<P>
Wu noted smooth cooperation between China and the Conference,
and pointed to the fact that the Chinese government and the
Conference successfully held a seminar on investment for small and
medium-sized businesses in developing Asian countries in Kunming
last October.
</P>
<P>
Ricupero told Wu that his organization places emphasis on its
cooperation with China. He spoke highly of China's role in
stabilizing the Asian economy and the global economy at large.
</P>
<P>
He said that the Second China Fair for International Investment
and Trade will set a good example for economic and trade
cooperation between countries. He wished the fair a complete
success.  
</P>
