<HEADLINE> Preparatory Committee Panel Ends Meeting in Macao </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, September 7 (Xinhua) -- The administrative working group
 of the Preparatory Committee for the Macao Special Administrative
 Region (SAR) ended its fourth meeting here Monday.
</P>
<P>
A communique released Monday afternoon said that the fourth
meeting continued discussion on the framework of the Macao SAR
government after Macao's return to the motherland on December 20,
1999, and some other relevant questions.
</P>
<P>
These questions are of great significance to Macao's steady
transition and smooth transfer of power, according to the
communique.
</P>
<P>
It said that from September 3 to 6, the working group consulted
Macao people in various social sectors about their opinions on the
formation of the Selection Committee which will produce the first
Macao SAR government.
</P>
<P>
The consultation, attended by more than 900 people from over
300 social bodies in Macao, was successful and laid a solid
foundation for upcoming work of the Preparatory Committee, the
communique said.
</P>
<P>
Macao residents were enthusiastic about the consultation and
put forward many views and suggestions on forming the Selection
Committee, showing their love of Macao and the motherland, it
said.
</P>
<P>
The administrative working group will conscientiously study the
opinions and draw up a detailed method on forming the Selection
Committee. The method will be discussed and adopted at a plenary
meeting of the Preparatory Committee, the communique said.
</P>
<P>
It was the first time for the administrative working group to
convene a meeting in Macao. 
</P>
</TEXT>
