<HEADLINE> Assailants on Iranian Cabinet Ministers Arrested </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, September 7 (Xinhua) -- Some main assailants on two
cabinet members have been identified and arrested by the security
forces, Iran's Interior Ministry announced on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Issuing a statement, the public relations office of the
Interior Ministry said that some others suspected of being
involved in the assaults are now being interrogated, the official
news agency IRNA reported.
</P>
<P>
However, the report did not mention how many people were
arrested and interrogated so far.
</P>
<P>
Iran's moderate Minister of Culture and Islamic Guidance
Ataollah Mohajerani and Vice President for Development and Social
Affairs Abdollah Nouri were beaten up by some assailants on Friday
while participating in the funeral procession for 700 soldiers
killed in the Iran-Iraq war (1980-88).
</P>
<P>
The statement expressed regret over the violence and lauded
the people for cooperation in identifying the culprits.
</P>
<P>
After the incident, President Mohammad Khatami and the supreme
leader Ayatollah Ali Khamenei ordered to identify and arrest those
involving in the assaults.
</P>
<P>
Mohajerani and Nouri, two main advocates of the open-minded
policies of Khatami's government, have been under harsh criticism
of the hard-line and conservative factions during the past months.
</P>
<P>
Nouri was ousted as interior minister by the conservative
Majlis (parliament) in June. Some conservatives also warned to
impeach Mohajerani for his policy on freedom of expression.
</P>
</TEXT>
