<HEADLINE> State Councillor Wu Yi Meets With Hong Kong Businessmen </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XIAMEN, September 7 (Xinhua) -- State Councillor Wu Yi met here
today with Hong Kong businessmen attending the 2nd China Fair for
International Investment Trade.
</P>
<P>
"Although Hong Kong investment in the inland areas has
decreased in the first half of this year because of the Asian
financial crisis, it still remains at a relatively high level," Wu
said.
</P>
<P>
According to statistics, from January to July the inland areas
have used Hong Kong investment for more than 4,700 projects, with
the contractual funds reaching 8.715 billion U.S. dollars, and a
total of 10.727 billion U.S. dollars has been used, including some
pledged before.
</P>
<P>
These figures have shown Hong Kong's confidence in inland
areas' economic development, Wu said.
</P>
<P>
"Hong Kong business people regard the market in the inland
areas as attractive and hope to gain more commercial opportunities
in this fair," said Herbert H.Y. Liang, chairman of the Chinese
Manufacturers Association of Hong Kong. 
</P>
