<HEADLINE> Beijing Banquet Marks DPRK Founding Anniversary </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 7 (Xinhua) -- Song Pong Hwan, charge
d'affaires ad interim of DPRK embassy in Beijing, held a banquet
this evening to mark the 50th anniversary of the founding of the
Democratic People's Republic of Korea (DPRK).
</P>
<P>
Chinese Vice-President Hu Jintao attended the banquet.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the occasion on behalf of the Communist Party of
China, Chinese government and people, Hu, who is also a member of
the Standing Committee of the Political Bureau of the Central
Committee of the Chinese Communist Party, congratulated Kim Jong
Il on his election of the Chairman of the National Defense
Commission (NDC) and on the 50th anniversary of the founding of
DPRK.
</P>
<P>
He said that the founding of DPRK is a major event in the
Korean history. He added that the Korean people have since then
embarked on the road of independently building a socialist country.
</P>
<P>
Hu spoke highly of the achievements that the Korean people,
under the leadership of the late President Kim Il Sung, Kim Jong
Il and the Workers' Party of Korea, have scored in both revolution
and national construction as well as in safeguarding national
sovereignty and dignity.
</P>
<P>
