<HEADLINE> Hail Storm Hits Beijing; No Damage Reported </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 7 (Xinhua) -- A burst of hailstones fell on
the Chinese capital at about 9:30 p.m. today, but no damage was
reported.
</P>
<P>
Sources from the Beijing Meteorological Bureau said that the
hail lasted for 5-to-6 minutes. The hailstones were quite small
with a diameter of 10 millimeters.
</P>
<P>
The hailstones fell on the west area of Beijing, and many
curious citizens ran out of their houses to watch.
</P>
<P>
Sources said that Beijing has been struck by hailstones several
times this year, but all the previous ones landed in mountainous
suburbs. This is the first time the hailstones found their way
into downtown Beijing.
</P>
<P>
But this was a normal meteorological phenomena, and citizens
should not worry, sources said, adding that it is hard to predict
if more hail will fall in Beijing. 
</P>
</TEXT>
