<HEADLINE> Jakarta Students Stage Anti-Government Protest </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, September 7 (Xinhua) -- Thousands of students from
Greater Jakarta staged an anti-government rally at the House of
Representatives (DPR) here Monday to protest the price hikes of
basic commodities which have been spiraling in the past few weeks.
</P>
<P>
The protesters, consisting of students from 46 state and
private universities, expressed their distrust over the
incapability of the government to lower the price hikes.
</P>
<P>
"There should have been a massive graft in the distribution of
nine basic necessaries and we demand accountability from the
government," field coordinator of the rally Mathias said.
</P>
<P>
Apart from that, he said, the price protest is triggered by a
statement by former president Soeharto Sunday night saying he had
no personal fortune stashed both overseas and at home.
</P>
<P>
Soeharto's denial had made the students so furious that they
should make something, Mathias said.
</P>
<P>
Beside demanding lowering the prices of basic commodities, the
students also called for the establishment of a transitional
administration with its members coming from all walks of life and
being trusted by the people.
</P>
<P>
This is the second biggest rally at the DPR building after that
of May which forced Soeharto to step down. 
