<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Minister Meets with Int'l Investment Fair Participants </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XIAMEN, September 7 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Minister of Foreign
Trade and Economic Cooperation Shi Guangsheng met here today with
major participants attending the Second China Fair for
International Investment and Trade scheduled for Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Shi said that the fair is the most important event for
attracting overseas investment in China. China's 31 provinces,
autonomous regions and cities have sent delegations to attend the
fair, offering 13,000 project items for overseas business people.
</P>
<P>
Shi said that although the country has been affected by the
Asian financial crisis and severe floods this year, China has made
remarkable achievements in using overseas capital.
</P>
<P>
In the first seven months, contracted foreign investment
increased by seven percent over the same period last year, he
said, adding that it will contribute to reaching this year's
economic goal of 8 percent.
</P>
<P>
Shi noted that there are abundant natural resources in China's
middle and west parts, which are a great place and a new area for
overseas business people to pour in money.
</P>
<P>
Participants in the fair are from leading companies of the
United States, Japan and other countries, as well as China's Hong
Kong Special Administrative Region and Taiwan region. 
</P>
</TEXT>
