<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 17 Killed in Bus Accident in S. Africa </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, September 7 (Xinhua) -- Seventeen people were
killed and at least 80 others injured when a passenger bus
collided with a truck in South Africa's North-West Province
Monday morning.
</P>
<P>
"We're still investigating the cause of the accident, but we
suspect that one of the vehicles veered out of its lane,
resulting in a head-on collision," said Louis Jacobs, a police
spokesman.
</P>
<P>
Sixteen people died instantly and a 17th man died in hospital
shortly after admission, South African Press Association (SAPA)
reported.
</P>
<P>
Seventy-one of the injured were treated and discharged, but
nine were critically injured.
</P>
<P>
Police said that the bus, transporting workers to their place
of employment, collided with the truck loaded with cement on the
outskirts of Lichtenburg, some 200 kilometers west of
Johannesburg. 
</P>
</TEXT>
