<HEADLINE> HKSFC Supports SAR Government Measures to Strengthen Market Regulation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 7 (Xinhua) -- The Securities and Futures
Commission (SFC) of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region
(SAR) welcomes the measures announced here Monday by the financial
secretary to tighten market discipline and strengthen confidence
in the securities and futures markets, the SFC announced here
Monday.
</P>
<P>
A statement issued by the SFC said it supports the government's
proposals and will work closely with the government and market
bodies to implement these measures.
</P>
<P>
The SFC statement said it will work with the Exchanges and
Clearing Houses to implement the measures put forward by the
government. Some of the measures can be implemented in the short
term while others will require approval by the boards of the each
of the market bodies and the SFC before they can be implemented.
</P>
<P>
The SFC will work expeditiously to complete the program as soon
as practicable, it said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
