<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Cambodian Police Open Fire at Protesters </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PHNOM PENH, September 7 (Xinhua) -- Cambodian police Monday
opened fire at opposition protesters outside the Cambodiana Hotel
here, killing at least one person and wounding many others.
</P>
<P>
The protester was rushed to hospital in a United Nations
vehicle and declared dead on arrival with a bullet wound to the
head, U.N. Center for Human Rights staff said.
</P>
<P>
A pool of blood soaked the ground where he fell after police
fired a long volley of shots into the air.
</P>
<P>
Hundreds of policemen armed with submachine guns opened fire
after they failed to disperse Sam Rainsy supporters outside the
hotel with batons.
</P>
<P>
The protesters gathered outside the hotel after Second Prime
Minister Hun Sen ordered the arrest of Sam Rainsy, leader of the
Sam Rainsy Party, and other opposition leaders, following a
grenade blast in Hun Sen's residence here.
</P>
<P>
Rainsy declared himself under U.N. protection. He is staying at
the U.N. Secretary General Representative office (UNSGR) in the
Cambodiana hotel where he spent the afternoon in talks with Kofi
Annan's representative and diplomats. 
</P>
</TEXT>
