<HEADLINE> Sensitive Index on BSE Rises 76.83 points </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, September 7 (Xinhua) -- The sensitive index on the
Bombay Stock Exchange (BSE) market Monday closed at 3,051.93
points as against last Friday's close of 2,975.10, netting a sharp
rise of 76.83 points.
</P>
<P>
The national index rose 33.12 points to 1,356.37 from previous
close of 1,323.25.
</P>
<P>
The BSE-200 and the U.S. dollar index were quoted substantially
up at 313.48 and 122.66 points compared with last weekend close of
306.11 and 119.80 respectively.
</P>
<P>
Equities rallied smartly lifting the sensitive index by 77
points on the opening day of the new account on the stock market
Monday in the wake of fresh buying from operators as well as
foreign institutional investors. 
</P>
</TEXT>
