<HEADLINE> American National Shot Dead in Philippines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, September 7 (Xinhua) -- A group of armed men shot and
killed an American national in an ambush Monday in a province
north of Manila, police said.
</P>
<P>
This developed as policemen and soldiers braced for terrorist
attacks on American targets by Muslims sympathetic to Saudi
billionaire Osama Bin Laden whom the United States suspected of
ordering the bombing of U.S. embassies in Kenya and Tanzania.
</P>
<P>
Police said the unknown assailants fired with armalite rifles
at Allen William Ericson, 60, a construction manager who was
driving a van from a project site in the village of Calumpit,
Tarlac province.
</P>
<P>
Police said Ericson, manager of Mags Metro Developing
Construction Corp., a subsidiary of U.S.-based construction firm
Das-Sand Corp., died on arrival at a nearby hospital due to bullet
wounds in the left armpit and stomach. 
</P>
</TEXT>
