<DOCNO> XIE19980907.0057 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese President Hails Victory over Floods (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 7 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin
urged people in the flood-affected areas to keep up their spirit
of fighting floods in rebuilding their homeland and promoting
economic development.
</P>
<P>
Jiang made the remark during an inspection tour to Jiangxi
Province, an area that suffered heavy losses during the summer
flooding.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said that the great battle against heavy floods in both
northern and southern China during the past two months has aroused
common concern of the whole Party, the whole army and all the
people of China.
</P>
<P>
"This is the second time I have come to the forefront of the
anti-flood fight along the Yangtze River," Jiang said. "I've sent
army troops to assist the anti-flood fight and postponed my visits
to Russia and Japan scheduled for early this month."
</P>
<P>
The Yangtze River experienced an unusually big flood along the
whole stretch of the river system, the worst since 1954. Eight
flood crests surged down the Yangtze River and, as a result, the
water level at ports in the middle and lower reaches of the
Yangtze River all surpassed the danger mark.
</P>
<P>
Floods on the Nenjiang and Songhua rivers in northeast China
were the biggest ever recorded in the region's history.
</P>
<P>
Preliminary reports indicate that 29 provinces, autonomous
regions and municipalities have been damaged by the floods in
varying degrees this year. According to official figures, the
floods were blamed for the deaths of 3,004 people, inundated 21
million hectares of farmland, destroyed nearly 5 million houses
and cost at least 166.6 billion yuan (about 20.8 billion U.S.
dollars) in economic losses.
</P>
<P>
"It is rare in China's history that a number of major rivers
flood at the same time, and that the flood crests had such a
mighty force and were sustained for such a long time," Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
Under the staunch leadership of the Party Central Committee,
Jiang said, the Chinese people, PLA soldiers and armed police
fought the flood with one mind and one heart.
</P>
<P>
In the past two months, he said, they have defeated flood
crests one after another and succeeded in protecting the safety of
major river dikes, cities, key railway lines and people's lives
and property, winning a decisive victory.
</P>
<P>
Though this year's flooding is bigger than 1931, the losses
incurred were much smaller. This can be attributed to the
important role played by the PLA, which is worthy of the title of
"an iron and steel great wall protecting the state and the people".
</P>
<P>
China is a nation with a glorious tradition of making
unremitting efforts and having a great cohesion, he said.
</P>
<P>
"The anti-flood battle proves that the CPC is a great, glorious
and correct Party," Jiang said. "The socialist system has great
superiority. The army is trustworthy. The Chinese people are
industrious and courageous.
</P>
<P>
"With such a good Party, army and people, all historical merits
can be created. So long as we unite more closely and work for a
common goal, we are sure to fulfill the cross-century program."
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
