<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Dominates Fin-Swimming Worlds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BOGOTA, September 6 (Xinhua) -- China confirmed their status
as a fin-swimming powerhouse by dominating the ninth world
championships which concluded in the Colombian city Cali on
Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese fin-swimmers took a lion's share of the medals at
stake, chopping up 16 golds, 9 silver and 3 bronze medals in the
total of 24 events.
</P>
<P>
Russia finished second on the overall table with a 5-5-7
record. Hungary came in third with a 3-2-2.
</P>
<P>
The tenth fin-swimming worlds will be held in Barcelona, Spain
in the year 2000. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980907.0059 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese President Hails Victory over Floods (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Jiang said that this year, because the affected areas were vast
and the time for the devastation was longer, the losses were quite
heavy.
</P>
<P>
Jiangxi, Hunan, Hubei, Heilongjiang and Jilin provinces as well
as the Inner Mongolia Autonomous Region suffered serious losses,
Jiang said, and the need to resume production and build housing is
urgent and arduous.
</P>
<P>
Thus, he said, the government at various levels should pay more
attention to jobs and adopt effective measures in their work.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out the favorable conditions during the final stage
of the battle against the floods such as the CPC Central Committee's
leadership, the self-reliance and joint efforts of the people in
the flood-hit areas, the aid from all over the country, and the
strong material and technical basis which has evolved during the
last 20 years of development.
</P>
<P>
He called for mobilizing people's initiative in the flood-hit
areas and the forces of all sectors.
</P>
<P>
Jiang also called for vigilance as the floods recede and urged
the PLA troops to uphold their heroic and unyielding spirit to
achieve the final victory over the floods.
</P>
<P>
Governments at various levels face an urgent task in making
adequate arrangements for the daily life of people in the
flood-hit areas, he said. Effective measures must be adopted, he
said, to ensure that people have adequate food, clothing, clean
water, housing and medical treatment.
</P>
<P>
Before winter arrives, flood victims should be moved into
houses or make-shift shelters and receive coats and quilts.
</P>
<P>
On the epidemic prevention work, Jiang said that historically
epidemics often occur after great disasters. Because of great
efforts, he said, there have been no serious epidemics in the
flood areas.
</P>
<P>
He urged the health departments to enhance supervision and
control over epidemics and ensure the supply of medicine and
medical instruments needed in the flood-stricken areas.
</P>
<P>
The epidemic prevention work should be carried on for an
extensive period and long-term preparations are expected to be
made ideologically, organizationally and materially, he said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980907.0060 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese President Hails Victory over Floods (3) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Jiang stressed the importance of maintaining a sound public
order and construction of water conservation projects in the
flooded areas. He also encouraged people in the areas to keep
their losses to a minimum.
</P>
<P>
The final solution to the problems in the development of
production and people's life in the flooded areas lies in the
people themselves, he said, calling on relief work to be based on
self-reliance and hard work.
</P>
<P>
On the domestic situation, Jiang said the general situation in
China is sound. In the first half of this year, China's Gross
Domestic Product grew by 7 percent. The growth rate decreased
slightly from the same period last year, he said, but it was still
among the highest in the world. China's export volume rose 6.9
percent and the exchange rate for the Renminbi was stable, Jiang
said.
</P>
<P>
However, it will still be arduous for China to achieve its
economic targets for this year, he added.
</P>
<P>
He said that to promote economic growth, the CPC Central
Committee has decided to adopt more active financial measures to
enhance infrastructure construction on the basis of major measures
set at the beginning of this year.
</P>
<P>
He said that it is a long-term strategy for the Chinese nation
to build water conservation projects. In the flood-control
struggle this year, the water conservation facilities built in the
past five decades, especially those built in recent years, played
an important role, he said.
</P>
<P>
Jiang called for overall planning and a long-term strategy in
water conservation construction on the basis of scientific
research and feasibility studies.
</P>
<P>
A top priority is to increase investment in the projects and
accelerate the harnessing of large rivers and lakes, including the
Yangtze and Yellow rivers, he said.
</P>
<P>
Without its own spiritual pillar, he said, a nation will have
no vitality or cohesion.
</P>
<P>
Commenting on the anti-flood struggle, he said that the Party,
the PLA and the people all demonstrated their determination to
overcome all difficulties, and that their courage with one heart
and one mind to fight against the flood was the upholding of
patriotism, collectivism and socialism advocated by the CPC.
</P>
<P>
It also demonstrates the national spirit of the Chinese nation
and the development of the spirit in contemporary China, he said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
