<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Yeltsin Proposes Trial Period for Chernomyrdin </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, September 7 (Xinhua) -- Russian President Boris Yeltsin
Monday proposed a six to eight-month trial for acting prime
minister Viktor Chernomyrdin, the Interfax news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Yeltsin made the suggestion in a just-ended roundtable meeting
in the Kremlin with the representatives of the State Duman in an
apparent attempt to head off a show-off with the parliament.
</P>
<P>
"There is no other candidate who, like Chernomyrdin, would have
such great experience in governing the country," said presidential
spokesman Sergei Yastrzhembsky.
</P>
<P>
The Communists, the biggest party in the Duma, rejected
Yeltsin's proposal despite long talks in the Kremlin and said they
would reject Chernomyrdin.
</P>
<P>
The State Duma, voted against Chernomyrdin as prime minister in
the first round of vote on August 31.
</P>
<P>
The second vote on Chernomyrdin as prime minister by the Duma
is to be held at 17:00 Moscow time on Monday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
