<HEADLINE> Number of Overseas-Funded Firms in China Reaches 310,000 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XIAMEN, September 7 (Xinhua) -- China has so far approved
310,000 overseas-funded firms with a contracted overseas
investment of 540 billion U.S. dollars, and the actually used
investment has hit 240 billion U.S. dollars, according to the
Chinese Ministry of Foreign Trade and Economic Cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Liu Zuozhang, an official with the ministry, announced at a
news conference here today that overseas investment had rebounded
after dropping for three consecutive years.
</P>
<P>
From January to July this year, contracted overseas investment
reached 28.18 billion U.S. dollars, up 7.25 percent over the same
period last year.
</P>
<P>
Liu said that China will open its second overseas investment and
trade fair Tuesday in Xiamen, capital of the southern province of
Fujian.
</P>
<P>
All Chinese provinces, cities and autonomous regions will send
delegations to the event. Liu said that more than 1,000 contracts
are expected to be signed, with the total overseas investment
expected to reach several billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Some of the world's biggest companies such as Motorola, Nokia,
Mobil and Panasonic plan to attend the fair.
</P>
<P>
Liu said the number of overseas participants has slightly
increased despite the Asian financial crisis. 
</P>
</TEXT>
