<HEADLINE> Chinese Companies to Build Roads in Bangladesh </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, September 7 (Xinhua) -- Two Chinese companies will help
Bangladesh build roads on the west side of the northwestern
Bangabandhu Jamuna Multipurpose Bridge to bring the bridge into
full play in developing the economy in the northwestern part of
the country.
</P>
<P>
The China Road and Bridge Corporation and the China Harbor
Engineering Company will construct 25 and 14 kilometers
respectively of the 55-kilometer road linking the Jamuna Bridge,
the country's longest bridge which was inaugurated in June this
year, with northwestern Bangladesh.
</P>
<P>
Liu Hong and Lu Chengfeng, representing the two Chinese
companies respectively, signed the contracts here Monday on behalf
of their respective companies with Abdul Wadud, chief engineer of
the Roads and Highways Department under the Bangladeshi Ministry
of Communication.
</P>
<P>
The construction of the World Bank-funded road would start
later this year or early next year and would be completed within
two to three years. 
</P>
