<HEADLINE> Bulletin Cambodian Police Open Fire at Protesters </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PHNOM PENH, September 7 (Xinhua) -- Cambodian police Monday
opened fire at opposition protesters outside the Cambodiana Hotel
in the centre of the city, killing at least one person and
wounding many others.
</P>
<P>
Hundreds of policemen armed with submachine guns opened fire
after they failed to disperse thousands of Sam Rainsy supporters
outside the hotel with batons.
</P>
<P>
The protesters gathered outside the hotel after Second Prime
Minister Hun Sen ordered to arrest Sam Rainsy, leader of the Sam
Rainsy Party, and other opposition leaders, following a grenade
blast in Hun Sen's residence here.
</P>
<P>
Sam Rainsy was now believed to be in the hotel with some
foreign ambassadors, including the ambassadors of the United
States, Canada, France and Singapore. The ambassadors stayed
there to have an emergency consultation about Cambodia's critical
situation. 
</P>
