<HEADLINE> Injuried French Gendarme Improving </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, September 7 (Xinhua) -- The condition of a French
gendarme who was left in a coma after a vicious attack by German
hooligans during the World Cup is improving, hospital sources
said.
</P>
<P>
The 43-year-old Daniel Nivel is now able to take a few steps
at a time and can say a few words.
</P>
<P>
Nivel had spent six weeks in a coma with severe head injuries
after being clubbed and kicked by a group of hooligans in the
city of Lens on the night of the Germany-Yugoslavia match on June
21.
</P>
<P>
Two Germans are being held in France on suspicion of attempted
murder in the attack and a further four in Germany in connection
with the incident. 
