<HEADLINE> Yangtze and Songhua Waters Remain High </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 7 (Xinhua) -- More than 3.12 million
soldiers and civilians are patroling along the main dikes of
the Yangtze and Songhua rivers as water levels at many sections
remain above the danger line.
</P>
<P>
By 2:00 p.m. today, the water level at Lianhuatang was 34.21
meters, 2.21 meters above the danger mark.
</P>
<P>
The water levels at Luoshan and Hankou in Hubei Province, Datong
in Anhui Province, Chenglingji near Dongting Lake and Hukou near
Poyang Lake all remain above the danger marks.
</P>
<P>
The water level of Nanjing in east China's Jiangsu Province was
9.65 meters at 1:15 pm today, surpassing the danger mark.
</P>
<P>
In northeast China, the water level at Harbin on the mainstream
of the Songhua River was 119.54 meters today, 1.44 meters above
the danger line.  
</P>
