<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HK's New Measures to Strengthen Currency System Welcomed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 7 (Xinhua) -- Different sectors in Hong
Kong all expressed their firm support for a package of the
government's seven technical measures to strengthen the currency
board and end manipulation of local interest rates by speculators.
</P>
<P>
Local newspapers reported here on Sunday or Monday that bankers
broadly welcomed the new measures announced on Saturday by the
Hong Kong Monetary Authority (HKMA), the de facto central bank in
Hong Kong, saying that the seven-point measures will help enlarge
the monetary base for defense against speculative attacks on the
HK dollar and make Hong Kong's financial system more stable and
sound.
</P>
<P>
The South China Morning Post said that its undertaking to
convert clearing accounts at a fixed exchange rate of 7.75 HK
dollars to 1 U.S. dollar and the rule to allow unlimited use of
the borrowing facility at the new Discount Window will "greatly
improve short-term liquidity to counteract manipulation of
interest rates."
</P>
<P>
Wen Wei Po described the government measures as a greatly
important and practical reform after the government summed up both
experiences and lessons.
</P>
<P>
The package of measures will create an condition to decrease
the interest rates so as to adapt Hong Kong's financial market to
the current downward economic readjustment, the paper said.
</P>
<P>
The Hong Kong Commercial Daily said in an editorial that the
new measures which become effective starting from Monday will
surely intensify the linked exchange rates and boost the Hong Kong
people's confidence in its economic recovery.
</P>
<P>
It expressed the belief that the Hong Kong stock market and
foreign exchange market will give an active response to them.
</P>
<P>
Other local newspapers also published commentaries and
editorials to support the government measures. Hong Kong
entrepreneurs from property and securities sectors as well as
Legislative Council members all spoke highly of these measures.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
