<DOCNO> XIE19980907.0104 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Measures to Tighten up Securities, Futures Markets </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 7 (Xinhua) -- Rebecca Lai, acting
secretary for Financial Services, outlined a 30-point program to
tighten up the disciplines in the securities and futures markets
here Monday.
</P>
<P>
Lai said at a Financial Affairs Panel meeting of the
Legislative Council that the program involves a total of five
securities and futures bodies in Hong Kong and aims to strengthen
regulation and enforcement on short selling, enhance risk
management across the financial markets and step up enforcement on
T+2 settlement rules.
</P>
<P>
Under these rules, shares including those sold short must be
delivered no later than two days after the trade is executed.
</P>
<P>
The program also calls for heavier penalties on breaches of
securities legislation and market rules in relation to naked and
unreported short selling and default in settlement.
</P>
<P>
It also commissions urgent studies on regulation over
custodians and registrars as well as over stock lending and
borrowing activities, the feasibility of full investor
participation in central Clearing and Settlement System and a
scripless securities market in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Financial Secretary Donald Tsang stressed at the meeting that
the government is absolutely determined to protect the stability
and integrity of the currency and financial markets of Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
The government continues to be fully committed to its free
economy policy and there will be no foreign exchange controls in
Hong Kong, he said.
</P>
<P>
The Program, together with the seven technical measures
announced by the Hong Kong Monetary Authority last Saturday
regarding the strengthening of the currency board system, form a
comprehensive plan to improve the ability of Hong Kong's monetary
and financial systems to withstand cross-market manipulation by
market players, Tsang said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980907.0105 </DOCNO>
