<HEADLINE> Kuala Lumpur Stocks Close Sharply Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, September 7 (Xinhua) -- Share prices on the Kuala
Lumpur Stock Exchange (KLSE) closed sharply higher Monday as
investors went on a buying spree following streams of positive
developments locally.
</P>
<P>
A strong surge buying frenzy enveloped the KLSE Monday as both
local and foreign players went on a buying spree and lifted the
market.
</P>
<P>
The Statistics Department Monday said that Malaysia posted a
trade surplus of 4.1 billion ringgit (1.079 billion U.S. dollars)
for July instilled more confidence in players, according to
dealers.
</P>
<P>
At the close, the 100-quality stocks Composite Index was pushed
up 22.457 percent or 81.62 points to 445.06, the all-share Emas
Index rose 19.74 points to 115.55, the Industrial Index increased
131.84 points to 861.26 and the second board added 15.54 points to
105.85.
</P>
<P>
Gainers thumped losers 832 to nine, while nine counters were
unchanged and 73 others untraded.
</P>
<P>
The day's turnover soared to 1.101 billion shares worth 1.577
billion ringgit (415 million U.S. dollars) compared with 522.449
million valued at 617.556 million ringgit (162.514 million U.S.
dollars) last Friday.
</P>
<P>
The main board turnover surged to 1.049 billion shares worth
1.497 billion ringgit (394 million U.S. dollars) from last
Friday's 498.522 million shares valued at 590.509 million ringgit
(155.397 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
The second board index expanded to 51.321 million shares worth
79.977 million ringgit (21.046 million U.S. dollars) from 23.928
million shares valued at 27.047 million ringgit (about 7.117
million U.S. dollars) last Friday.
</P>
<P>
However, off market fell to 3.455 million shares worth 6.125
million ringgit (1.611 million U.S. dollars) from last Friday's
6.780 million shares valued at 6.196 million ringgit (1.63 million
U.S. dollars) .
</P>
<P>
On sectoral basis, consumer products accounted for 48.014
million shares traded on the main board, industrial products
77.466 million shares, construction 126.107 million shares,
trade/services 276.507 million shares, infrastructures 2.495
million shares, finance 217.242 million shares, hotels 3.037
million shares, properties 107.633 million shares, plantation
18.413 million shares, mining 2.592 million shares, trusts 801,000
shares, closed/fund 475,000 shares and loans 169.142 million
shares. 
</P>
</TEXT>
