<HEADLINE> Hun Sen: Sam Rainsy to be Arrested </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PHNOM PENH, September 7 (Xinhua) -- Sam Rainsy, leader of
Cambodia's main opposition Sam Rainsy Party (SRP), will soon be
arrested by the government, Second Prime Minister Hun Sen said
Monday.
</P>
<P>
Hun Sen said at a press conference after he flew back from Siem
Reap that he had ordered to seal off the border, airports and
harbors to prevent the organizers and leaders of the
demonstrations from leaving the country. They will be arrested, he
added.
</P>
<P>
Asked if Sam Rainsy was included on the list, Hun Sen confirmed
it. However, he added that Prince Norodom Ranariddh's destiny will
be decided by the prosecutor.
</P>
<P>
The second premier took the reaction after his residence in
Phnom Penh was attacked on Monday morning by three hand-bombs, two
of which exploded. At that time Hun Sen was in Siem Reap.
</P>
<P>
Hun Sen also said that the government has ordered the
demonstrators gathering in front of the National Assembly to leave
before 24:00 local time on Monday evening. Otherwise, the
government will take action to deal with them.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, King Norodom Sihanouk, who is hosting a working
session in Siem Reap, also condemned the terrorism.
</P>
<P>
The King had wished to resolve the month-long political crisis
between the Cambodian People's Party led by Hun Sen and the
opposition of Funcipec and the SRP, and to form a new government
as soon as possible. 
</P>
</TEXT>
