<HEADLINE> Singapore Donates to Flood-Stricken Areas </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, Sept. 7 (Xinhua) -- President Sia Yong, on behalf of
the Singa-Sino Friendship Association, donated 50,000 Singapore
dollars to the flood-stricken areas of China here today.
</P>
<P>
Qi Huaiyuan, president of the Chinese People's Association for
Friendship with Foreign Countries, expressed his sincere gratitude
on behalf of the flood victims and said that the donation will be
sent to the flood victims as soon as possible.  
</P>
