Minister Mahmoud Vaezi said the Tehran meeting serves to boost
bonds linking the three countries and is not against any other
country.
</P>
<P>
He said the three countries would start cooperation in energy
sector, in countering natural disasters, and in communications and
transportation.
</P>
<P>
Political issues will also be discussed at the meeting, Vaezi
said, adding that the three countries foreign ministers are
scheduled to sign a final document on Wednesday. 
