<HEADLINE> 100th IPU Conference Opens in Kremlin </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, September 7 (Xinhua) -- The 100th Congress of the
Inter-Parliamentary Union (IPU) opened in the Kremlin Monday while
Russia's branch of power tried to break political stalemate in the
country.
</P>
<P>
Russian President Boris Yeltsin, just after a roundtable
meeting on nomination of Viktor Chernomyrdin, expressed his
"absolute confidence" that his country will manage to improve its
economic situation.
</P>
<P>
"I am absolutely certain that we shall improve the situation
and the main thing now is the search for international mechanisms
to neutralize the consequences of crisis for the population,"
Yeltsin told parliamentarian delegates from more than 130
countries.
</P>
<P>
Gennady Seleznyov, speaker of Russia's State Duma, or lower
house of parliament, said "there can be no full-fledged democracy
without a full-fledged parliament."
</P>
<P>
The roundtable meeting, participated by Yeltsin, acting prime
minister Viktor Chernomyrdin, Seleznyov, and Yegor Stroyev,
speaker of the Federation Council, or upper house of parliament,
will continue in the afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Sergei Yastrzhembsky, Yeltsin's spokesman, said participants at
the roundtable meeting agreed in the morning that "efficient,
rapid and coordinated decisions" should be made.
</P>
<P>
Stroyev told reporters during the break that "there were no
difficult moments" at the meeting. 
</P>
