<HEADLINE> Fujian's Non-Public Sector Important to Economic Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, September 7 (Xinhua) -- The non-public-owned sector has
become an important pillar of the economic growth in east China's
Fujian Province.
</P>
<P>
Fujian currently has more than 88,000 non-public-owned
businesses, which accounted for 37.8 percent of the provincial
gross domestic product last year, up from only 5.5 percent in
1978, the year China launched its reforms and opening-up.
</P>
<P>
Official figures also show that overseas-funded businesses made
up 60 percent of Fujian's total exports last year.
</P>
<P>
"The development of the non-public-owned sector has helped
inject vitality and vigor into the provincial economy and has
become an important motive force for rapid economic growth," said
Chen Mingyi, leader of the province.
</P>
<P>
The non-public-owned economic sector has also become an
employment pool. Official data indicate that overseas-funded firms
in Fujian employ 1.7 million people, while private sector hires
another 3.6 million. The combined figure represents nearly
two-thirds of Fujian' s labor force in the industrial and service
sectors.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
