<HEADLINE> Explosive PC Sales in Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, September 7 (Xinhua) -- Personal computers have
been entering Shanghai households at an explosive rate since the
start of the year, with more Shanghai people eagerly racing to
reap the benefits of the information age.
</P>
<P>
During the January-July period, 11,970 PCs were sold in
Shanghai, 93.3 percent more than the same period last year,
according to the Metropolitan Guide newspaper.
</P>
<P>
The Shanghai-based paper said that in July alone, 6,253 PCs
were sold, 3.3 times as many as the same month last year.
</P>
<P>
Officials of the city's commercial commission said that
individual households are playing a more dominant role in PC sales
as compared with institutional buyers.
</P>
<P>
To meet the strong demand for computers, China's largest
computer outlet, the Xielian Computer Market, will open later this
month. 
</P>
