<HEADLINE> Bangladeshi Parliament Begins 10th Session </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, September 7 (Xinhua) -- Bangladesh's 7th Jatiya Sangsad
(parliament) began its 10th session Monday afternoon amid a severe
flood situation in the country.
</P>
<P>
With the prolonged flood still ravaging the country, the
session, which was summoned to fulfill the constitutional
obligation and to discuss urgent issues only, was to be a "brief"
one, parliament sources said.
</P>
<P>
The session would then be adjourned for at least 10 days to
enable ministers and parliament members to supervise relief
activities in their respective constituencies.
</P>
<P>
Prime Minister Sheikh Hasina was expected to address the House
on the overall flood situation, relief activities and post-flood
rehabilitation plans.
</P>
<P>
The session may witness stormy debate between the Treasury
bench and the Opposition camp over issues such as the current
flood situation, law and order situation in the country, and the
recent deportation of two members of parliament from England.
</P>
<P>
The on-going flood, which has already lasted for nearly two
months, has ravaged about two-thirds of the country and left about
30 million of its 127 million people homeless or marooned. Up to
now, the death toll has risen to 584 in 47 of the country's 64
districts. 
</P>
</TEXT>
