<HEADLINE> China's Largest Gem and Jade Fair in Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, September 7 (Xinhua) -- China's largest gem and jade
fair will be held in this oriental metropolis of Shanghai from
September 29 to October 4.
</P>
<P>
Liu Zhenyuan, chairman of the Shanghai Gem and Jade
Association, said the fair will be jointly held by his association
and the China National Gem and Jade Association.
</P>
<P>
The event is designed to advance economic and trade
cooperation, scientific and cultural exchanges in the gem and jade
industry, and attract more professionals to help China's gem and
jade industry become become an important hard currency earner.
</P>
<P>
The main venue will be the new building of the First General
Merchandise Store on East Nanjing Road, where some 100 gem and
jade businessmen from Hong Kong, Taiwan and the mainland will
exhibit commodities including carved jadeware, gold, silver and
jade jewelry, ornamental stones and equipment for processing
precious and semi-precious stones.
</P>
<P>
The organizer of the fair will also open three specialized
branch venues for diamonds, jadeite, and crystals near
Chenghuangmiao. During the fair, a range of other activities
including a seminar on the market economy and the culture of
precious stones and jade will be held.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai plans to become a center for the processing and
import and export of precious stones and jade and a leading market
of precious stones and jade in Asia by the year 2010.
</P>
<P>
Last year, Shanghai chalked up two billion yuan (240 million US
dollars) of precious stones and jade. 
</P>
</TEXT>
