<HEADLINE> China Schedules Exhibition of General Merchandise </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, September 7 (Xinhua) -- China will launch an
exhibition of general merchandise from Oct. 28 to Nov. 1 in Yiwu,
a city in east Zhejiang Province.
</P>
<P>
The exposition is being jointly organized by the Zhejiang
Provincial Government, the State Light Industry Bureau and the
State Internal Trade Bureau and supported by the All-China
Federation for Industry and Commerce, the Hong Kong Trade
Development Council and the Chinese General Chamber of Commerce of
Macao.
</P>
<P>
Because of the effects of economic restructuring and prevailing
global economic sentiments, China's consumer goods market is
weak. The scheduled exhibition is intended to promote sales and
activate the market, according to an official source.
</P>
<P>
The source also said that more than 600 companies and more than
2,000 trade representatives are expected to participate in the
exposition.
</P>
<P>
Yiwu is well known in China as the home of the country's
largest and most developed wholesale sundries market, whose sales
average more than 20 billion yuan (2.4 billion US dollars) each
year. The market has established economic and trade contacts with
53 countries and regions. 
</P>
</TEXT>
