<HEADLINE> Electronics Industry Blooming in Northeast China Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, September 7 (Xinhua) -- With color TV as its main
product, the electronics industry in northest China's Liaoning
province has been developing rapidly in recent years.
</P>
<P>
The total output value of this industry in the province reached
7.42 billion yuan (896 million US dollars) in the first half of
this year, up 25 percent over that of the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
A provincial government official said the major characteristic
of the electronics industry in Liaoning is the rapid growth of
color TV production.
</P>
<P>
He noted that the color TV industry in Liaoning has established
cooperation with some of the world's brand-name companies such as
Toshiba and Hisense. The Dalian Television Plant now has an
annual production capability of one-million television sets for its
cooperation with Toshiba of Japan.
</P>
<P>
The electronics industry in Liaoning encompasses some 142
enterprises manufacturing a series of products from color TVs to
computers.  
</P>
