<HEADLINE> 4 Ugandan Kids Killed in Rally Crash </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, September 7 (Xinhua) -- Four children were killed and
23 people seriously injured in three separate car rally accidents
near Bombo town on Kampala-Gulu road Sunday, according to local
police.
</P>
<P>
Local police authorities said that the dead were aged 7, 9,
15, 14 respectively, the New Vision newspaper said Monday.
</P>
<P>
The first accident involves a Land-rover which rammed into the
four children who were watching the rally cars, killing them all
and injuring some others.
</P>
<P>
The driver tried to dodge a motorcyclist, police said, and
caused the truck overturn in the middle of the road, bringing the
busy traffic on the road to a standstill.
</P>
<P>
Within a few minutes, two other vehicles collided and some
passengers injured. However, the three drivers all fled the
scene.
</P>
<P>
Another vehicle, whose driver was said to have been drinking
and overspeeding, reportedly overturned at another place. A
rally spectator was hit by a tyre flown off the vehicle and got a
broken limb.
</P>
<P>
Instead of taking the injured to hospital, the onlookers ran
to guzzle the two remaining crates of beer which were in the
boot. 
</P>
