<HEADLINE> Rios Upset by Larsson in U.S. Open </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, September 6 (Xinhua) -- Magnus Larsson of Sweden
knocked out world number 2 player Marcelo Rios of Chile in five
sets at the U.S. Open tennis championships here tonight.
</P>
<P>
The 28-year-old unseeded veteran stormed back to beat Rios
6-1,6-7 (3-7), 2-6, 6-3, 6-2. Larsson broke Rios in fifth game of
the final set and won the last three games.
</P>
<P>
Rios was the hottest player on the men's tour earlier this
year,reaching the final of the Australian Open, winning 40 of 45
matches and twice moving past American Pete Sampras into the top
ranking.But since making the quarterfinals of the French Open in
May, Rios was only 11-7. Prior to the Open, Rios played in only
two events on hardcourts this summer and had only one match
victory.
</P>
<P>
Larsson, who is appearing in his seventh U.S. Open, matched
his best showing of last year, when he made the quarterfinals
before losing to eventual champion Patrick Rafter of Australia.
Larsson also made the quarterfinals in 1993. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
