<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hingis Enters Quarterfinals of U.S. Open </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, September 6 (Xinhua) -- Top seed Martina Hingis of
Switzerland stormed into the quarterfinals of the U.S. Open her
today by beating Nathalie Dechy of France 6-4, 6-4.
</P>
<P>
Hingis had her serve broken twice in the opening set and had
to rally from 2-4 to win. Hingis broke to tie the first set, held
at love to go up 5-4, and then broke again to take the set. Both
players were troubled by the gusting winds as Hingis committed 25
unforced errors and had seven double faults in the opening set
and Dechy made 28 unforced errors.
</P>
<P>
Hingis went down a break in the second set, then squandered a
break lead before finally putting away Dechy with a service break
in the final game.
</P>
<P>
Hingis needed one hour and 20 minutes to win the error-filled
match and hardly looked like the number one player in the world
as she bounced her racquet on the court several times in
frustration over mistakes and blasted the ball angrily into the
net after a close call went against her.
</P>
<P>
Hingis had 19 winners and 41 unforced errors while Dechy had
16 winners and 47 unforced errors. Hingis also committed one
double faults. 
</P>
