<HEADLINE> Seles Roars into U.S. Open Quarterfinals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, September 6 (Xinhua) -- Two-time champion Monica
Seles of the United States battled her way into the quarterfinals
with a 6-2, 4-6, 6-3 victory over fellow American Kimberly Po in
the U.S.Open tennis championships here today.
</P>
<P>
Seles, who is seeded sixth this year, took command early with
her power game, breaking Po on her first two service games and
surging to a 4-0 lead. Po, ranked 65th in the world, managed to
hold her service twice before Seles broke again and took the set.
</P>
<P>
Seles stormed to a 4-1 lead in the second set and looked to be
on her way to an easy victory, but Po rallied to win the next
game and held for a 3-2 with a spectacular running crosscourt
winner.Seles fought off a break point in the next game and held
for a 4-2 lead and then closed the match with another service in
the final game.
</P>
<P>
Po played aggressive tennis throughout but it cost her in the
heat and gusting winds as she connected for 40 winners but also
committed 50 unforced errors Po also had 10 chances to break but
was successful on three. Seles, meanwhile capitalized on her
chances, breaking Po on six of seven opportunities.
</P>
<P>
In another match, Jana Novotna of the Czech Republic defeated
number nine Irina Spirlea of Romania 6-3, 6-3 today to earn her
quarterfinal berth. She will meet Patty Schnyder of Switzerland
in the quarterfinals who upset Steffi Graf of Germany today.
</P>
