<HEADLINE> Malaysia Names New Central Bank Governor </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, September 7 (Xinhua) -- Director-General of the
Economic Planning Unit (EPU) in the Prime Minister's Department
Ali Abul Hassan Sulaiman was appointed new Governor of Bank Negara
(State Bank) Malaysia, the Finance Ministry announced here Monday.
</P>
<P>
The ministry also announced Zeti Akhtar Aziz, one of the
central bank's four assistant governors was appointed as the new
Deputy Governor of the central bank.
</P>
<P>
The appointments take effect from Monday, the ministry said in
a statement.
</P>
<P>
Ali Abul Hassan, 57, replaced Ahmad Mohamed Don who resigned on
September 1 while Zeti, 51, took over from Fong Weng Phak who also
resigned on the same day.
</P>
<P>
Zeti had been acting governor since the resignations of the top
two central bank officials.
</P>
<P>
Ali Abul Hassan was recently appointed Secretary to the
National Economic Action Council which spearheads the economic
recovery.
</P>
<P>
As EPU chief since 1991, he also oversees Malaysia's aggressive
thrust into privatization of government utilities, the biggest
being electricity and telecommunications.
</P>
<P>
Zeti's promotion as deputy governor is the highest position
achieved by a woman at the central bank. 
</P>
