<HEADLINE> Qingdao's Private Sector Shows Stable Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
QINGDAO, September 7 (Xinhua) -- The private sector of this
major port city of east China's Shandong Province has developed
steadily this year, official figures indicate.
</P>
<P>
Qingdao had 196,000 individually run businesses and 18,000
private enterprises by the end of June and together they employed
518,000 people, according to figures provided by the municipal
bureau for industry and commerce.
</P>
<P>
The number of firms each with a registered capital of more than
one million yuan (about 120,000 U.S. dollars) exceeded 2,700 for
the first half of this year, up more than 35 percent from the same
period last year.
</P>
<P>
While 78 percent of the individually run businesses are engaged
in the service sector, a rapidly increasing proportion of private
firms has charged into high-tech and export-oriented industries, a
bureau official said.
</P>
<P>
Official figures also show that the individually run businesses
and private firms in Qingdao turned in 254 million yuan in taxes
in the first six months of this year, a jump of 33.7 percent from
a year ago.  
</P>
