<HEADLINE> 8 Palestinians Arrested Following Clashes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, September 6 (Xinhua) -- Israeli police arrested
eight Palestinians in the Shufat refugee camp Sunday following
Saturday's clashes between Israeli police and refugees, the Israel
Radio said.
</P>
<P>
Palestinian refugee witnesses said that a large number of
policemen stormed the camp, north of Jerusalem, Sunday morning and
carried away eight young Palestinians.
</P>
<P>
Israeli police have the duty to maintain order in the camp and
more arrests will be carried out, the Radio quoted Israeli police
officers as saying.
</P>
<P>
The clashes erupted when an Israeli ambulance, which was called
to pick up a refugee patient, refused to enter the camp without
the escort of the Israeli police and the Palestinian died of heart
attack due to the delay of treatment.
</P>
<P>
The angered Palestinians threw stones and firebombs at the
ambulance and Israeli police, and the Israeli police fired back
with rubber bullets and tear gas, in which five Israeli policemen
and 15 Palestinians were injured.
</P>
<P>
The Palestinian side said that two of the injured Palestinians
are in critical condition, with a 45-year-old woman shot in the
throat with a rubber bullet. 
</P>
</TEXT>
