<HEADLINE> Ningxia College Trains Minorities in Agricultural Fields </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YINCHUAN, September 7 (Xinhua) -- The 40-year old Ningxia
Agricultural College, the first institute of higher education in
the Ningxia Hui Autonomous Region, has been recognized for its
contributions to local social and economic development.
</P>
<P>
The institute has so far trained more than 8,000 professionals,
70 percent of whom are ethnic students. The graduates are playing
important roles in agricultural development and farming
technology, water conservation, biological sciences and the food
industry.
</P>
<P>
With a school staff of 662, 1,600 students are studying in the
college's seven departments and 21 specialities ranging from
farming, gardening and veterinary science to agricultural
management and economics.
</P>
<P>
During the last 40 years, graduates from the college have
carried out hundreds of scientific and technological
projects. Many of them have won national prizes.
</P>
<P>
The college also has established cooperative relations with 28
universities and research institutes in the fields of training,
research and academic exchanges.  
</P>
