U.S. embassy in Moscow, the Interfax news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
He called police at 20:23 local time (1623 GMT) that a bomb was
planted in the building, Interfax said, quoting a source with the
city police department.
</P>
<P>
The embassy building has been cordoned off, and Moscow rescue
service and ambulances have been dispatched to the site.
</P>
<P>
With the consent of the American side, a policeman and a
trained dog are examining the building, Interfax said. (Russia-US
Embassy-Bomb Threat)
</P>
