<HEADLINE> Newcastle Deny Parma Move for Shearer </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, September 6 (Xinhua) -- Newcastle have dismissed
reports that Italian side Parma have launched a fresh bid to sign
Alan Shearer.
</P>
<P>
Italian newspaper Gazzetta dello Sport said the Serie A club
had stepped up their attempts to reunite the England captain with
former Magpie Faustino Asprilla.
</P>
<P>
The paper claimed Parma, who reportedly had an original offer
of 15 million pounds turned down in June, reopened negotiations
after Shearer's future was thrown into doubt following the
arrival of a new manager, Ruud Gullit.
</P>
<P>
But Newcastle are insisting that Shearer is going nowhere.
</P>
<P>
The club reiterated chief executive Freddie Fletcher's summer
statement that their prime asset is not for sale at any price and
refused to comment further on the reports.
</P>
<P>
Shearer, along with veteran defender Stuart Pearce and club
captain Rob Lee, is known to have met up with new boss Gullit
last week to discuss the future of the club in the wake of Kenny
Dalglish's dismissal. 
</P>
</TEXT>
