<HEADLINE> Mercedes Wins FIA GT Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, September 6 (Xinhua) -- Mercedes-Benz notched up the
1998 FIA GT title after German Bernd Schneider and Australia's
Mark Webber won the Donington 500km on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The victory secured Mercedes' seventh win in the seven races
of the 1998 series and confirmed the team's title for the second
consecutive year.
</P>
<P>
Schneider and Webber lead the drivers' series by seven points
but can still be caught by team mates Klaus Ludwig and Ricardo
Zonta with three races remaining in Austria, Florida and Califo
rnia.
</P>
<P>
Porsche had made a desperate effort to halt the Mercedes
steamroller at Donington Park as Scotland's Allan McNish and
Germany's Uwe Alzen shot past both front-row Mercedes at the
start.
</P>
<P>
But McNish had jumped the green light and earned a 10-second
penalty which cost him the lead.
</P>
<P>
Following are the results of the 125-lap Donington 500km:
</P>
<P>
1. Bernd Schneider, Germany/Mark Webber, Australia,
Mercedes,three hours five minutes 00.73 seconds, average speed
169.29kph
</P>
<P>
2. Klaus Ludwig, Germany/Ricardo Zonta, Brazil, Mercedes,
45.330 seconds behind
</P>
<P>
3. Allan McNish, Britain/Tannick Dalmas, France, Porsche, 124
laps
</P>
<P>
4. Uwe Alzen, Germany/Jorg Muller, Germany, Porsche, 123 laps
</P>
<P>
5. Jean-Marc Gounon, France/Marcel Tiemann, Germany, Persson
Mercedes, 123 laps
</P>
<P>
Fastest lap: Schneider one minute 25.550 seconds, 169.29kph
</P>
</TEXT>
